1.Environment Setup

Step 1.1: Install Required Packages
Windows Command Prompt - Complete Step-by-Step Guide
step 1:
Open Command Prompt
Press Windows Key + R on your keyboard
Type cmd in the box
Press Enter or click OK
What you'll see:
Text C:\Users\YourName>

Step 2: 
Navigate to Desktop
cmd
cd Desktop
What you'll see:
Text C:\Users\YourName\Desktop>

Step 3:
 Create Project Folder
cmd
mkdir network-log-translator
What you'll see:
Text C:\Users\YourName\Desktop>
(No message means it worked!)

Step 4: 
Enter the Project Folder
cmd
cd network-log-translator
What you'll see:
Text C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>

 Step 5: 
Create Virtual Environment
cmd
python -m venv venv
What you'll see:
Text C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>
(It will take 10-20 seconds with no output - this is normal!)

If you get "'python' is not recognized" error: You need to install Python first from python.org

Step 6:
 Activate Virtual Environment
cmd
venv\Scripts\activate
What you'll see:
Text (venv) C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>
✅ The (venv) at the beginning means it worked! This is VERY important.

Step 7:
 Create Subfolders
cmd
mkdir translator parsers detectors classifier data
What you'll see:
Text (venv) C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>

Step 8:
 Create init Files
cmd
type nul > translator\__init__.py
cmd
type nul > parsers\__init__.py
cmd
type nul > detectors\__init__.py
cmd
type nul > classifier\__init__.py
What you'll see after each:
Text (venv) C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>
(No message means it worked!)

Step 9:
Install Required Packages
cmd
pip install anthropic openai python-dotenv streamlit pandas scikit-learn colorama google-generativeai
What you'll see:
Text Collecting anthropic
  Downloading anthropic-0.49.0-py3-none-any.whl...
Collecting openai
  Downloading openai-1.70.0-py3-none-any.whl...
... (lots of installation text) ...
Successfully installed anthropic-0.49.0 openai-1.70.0 ... 
This will take 1-2 minutes. Wait for Successfully installed message.


Step 10: Verify Installation
Type this command and press Enter:
cmd
pip list
What you'll see text
Package                Version
---------------------- ---------
anthropic              0.49.0
google-generativeai    0.8.3
openai                 1.70.0
streamlit              1.42.0
... (and more packages)
✅ You're Done! Your Command Prompt Should Look Like This:
text
(venv) C:\Users\YourName\Desktop\network-log-translator>


 Next Steps - Create Your First File
Now you need to create Python files. Don't type these in Command Prompt! Instead:

use this command to create a blank file (then edit in Notepad):

cmd
notepad translator\llm_translate.py
🚨 Common Errors & Fixes
Error Message	What To Do
'python' is not recognized	Install Python from python.org, then RESTART Command Prompt
'pip' is not recognized	Same as above - Python not installed properly
The system cannot find the path specified	You mistyped a folder name. Type dir to see what folders exist
Access is denied	Right-click Command Prompt → "Run as administrator"
venv\Scripts\activate not working	Type cd venv\Scripts then activate then cd ..\..
💾 How to Save Your Work & Come Back Later
Tomorrow, when you open Command Prompt again:

cmd
cd Desktop\network-log-translator
venv\Scripts\activate
You'll see (venv) again and you're ready to continue!


Step 1.2: Get an API Key (Choose One)
Part 1: Install Ollama + Download Llama*

*Window 1: Command Prompt as Administrator*
1. Press `Windows + R`, type `cmd`, then press `Ctrl + Shift + Enter` to run as admin
2. Copy/paste these commands one by one, press Enter after each:
curl -L https://ollama.com/download/OllamaSetup.exe -o %USERPROFILE%\Downloads\OllamaSetup.exe
%USERPROFILE%\Downloads\OllamaSetup.exe
3. Follow the installer popup. Click Next → Install → Finish. Use default settings.

4. *Close that admin window.* Open a NEW normal Command Prompt: `Windows + R`, type `cmd`, Enter

5. Verify install:
ollama --version
You should see `ollama version 0.6.5` or similar.

6. Download Llama model. This takes 5-10 min and downloads ∼2GB:
ollama pull llama3.2:3b
7. Test it works:
ollama run llama3.2:3b "Say hello"
Press `Ctrl + C` to exit chat.

---

🪟Part 2: Set Up Your Project*

*Window 1: Command Prompt for project work*
1. Create project folder:
cd %USERPROFILE%\Desktop
mkdir network-log-translator
cd network-log-translator
2. Create virtual environment:
python -m venv venv
3. Activate it. You’ll see `(venv)` appear at start of line:
venv\Scripts\activate
4. Install packages:
pip install ollama python-dotenv streamlit pandas scikit-learn colorama requests
5. Create folders:
mkdir translator parsers detectors classifier data
6. Create empty `*init*.py` files:
type nul > translator\__init__.py
type nul > parsers\__init__.py
type nul > detectors\__init__.py
type nul > classifier\__init__.py
7. Create `translator\llm_translate.py` using notepad:
notepad translator\llm_translate.py
Paste the Python code from Step 1.4 above, Save, Close notepad.

Part 3: Start Ollama Server*

*Window 2: Open SECOND Command Prompt*
1. `Windows + R`, type `cmd`, Enter
2. Run this and *leave this window open*:
ollama serve
You’ll see `Listening on 127.0.0.1:11434`. Keep this running in background.

 Part 4: Test Everything Works*

*Back to Window 1: Your project window with `(venv)`*
python translator\llm_translate.py
*If successful you’ll see:*
🔍 Checking Ollama health...
✅ Ollama is ready!
📝 Translating test log...

📢 RESULT:

[CRITICAL]: 3,200 failed login attempts from IP 103.45.67.89...
⏱️ Translation time: 2.34 seconds
 Quick Resume Next Time*

Every time you work on this project, just do:
*Window 1:*
cd %USERPROFILE%\Desktop\network-log-translator
venv\Scripts\activate
*Window 2:*
ollama serve
Then run your code in Window 1.





